SUMMARY:Frink Ridge invasive plants removal
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a restoration work party at Frink Park. \nWe’re going to visit violence upon some invasive species today in preparation to replace them with native local species this fall. You can expect to be pulling out mostly ivy and holly. This site has been under restoration since 2022 so it’s a good place to see what’s been done and what your work area will look like a couple of years from now. \nRegister
URL:https://www.seattleparksfoundation.org/event/frink-ridge-invasive-plants-removal-2/
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://www.seattleparksfoundation.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/home-NEW-2-Catherine-Anstett-Trolls-Knoll-gloves.jpg
